						               													<description>A ruthless struggle for power in a small Spanish village. Accusations will fly as knives, impossible projects will come true and the sickening stench of corruption will be clearly noticed. The meanest face of politics in a card game for three to six players. A self-published free print and play game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of this game is prevail in the struggle for power in a small village. The winner will be the one who win the mayoralty in two elections.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The village is represented by seven scene's cards, different in every match. They represent activities and places that give votes to players. Sometimes, they will have the chance of change them by their own projects for strenghten their own voting base and weaken his opponents at the same time. When it happens, players must negotiate which of the scene cards will be substituted by the new project. If necessary, they vote if each project is accepted or rejected.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take cards of a deck and use them by turns for attacking, defend themselves and take new votes and cards. If they obtain the Opportunity card they will have the chance to execute one of their projects. If they have (and decide to use) the Temptation card, they will choose one of the corruption cards, which purpose is to buy votes or councilors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the third round, it's time to elections. Players count their votes and assign to each one the members of the town hall. If a player is elected for second time, wins the match.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
